    "lesson_connection": "advantage-or-reset",
    "explanation_md": "**Advantage or Reset — same read, other side.** A short closeout is a short closeout. Left wing, right wing — the cue is his cushion, not your spot. When the defender's feet are still pointed at the ball and his hands aren't up, the shot is open before his second step. **Catch in your pocket. Lift. Release.**",
